alt_text:
An asexual person feels no sexual attraction.
Similarly, a demisexual person does not experience sexual attraction to someone, unless they have a deep, emotional / platonic connection/bond with them first.
A third similar sexuality is greysexual, which is like asexual, but the person experiences attraction just sometimes or not strongly. I ran out of pictures to add the grey flag but it looks similar, just without black.
